Rating: 3
I've made this several times and love it! Sometimes I use regular eggplant and cut it into slices a little less than half-inch to make it cook faster. Sometimes I brown the eggplant on a flat skillet until it's done. The fish sauce is really great -- just the right blend of sweet and sour and the mint gives it a really surprising flavor. And because you can serve it at room temperature, it's very convenient to make for cook-outs.